[This didn't work.]

Build SRC Modula-3:
  http://research.compaq.com/SRC/modula-3/html/release36.html

(Alternately:
  http://research.compaq.com/SRC/modula-3/html/srcm3.html
  Installation instructions:
    http://research.compaq.com/SRC/modula-3/html/install-POSIX.html


# Note the use of http instead of ftp in the wget commands below.
cd ~/bin/src
mkdir modula3
cd modula3
wget http://gatekeeper.dec.com/pub/DEC/SRC/Modula-3/release-3.6/boot-LINUXELF.tar.gz
wget http://gatekeeper.dec.com/pub/DEC/SRC/Modula-3/release-3.6/m3cc.tar.gz
wget http://gatekeeper.dec.com/pub/DEC/SRC/Modula-3/release-3.6/m3.tar.gz
tar xzf boot-LINUXELF.tar.gz
tar xzf m3cc.tar.gz
tar xzf m3.tar.gz
mv m3cc boot-LINUXELF

# Edit file boot-LINUXELF/m3build/templates/LINUXELF

perl -pi.bak -e 's:/usr/X11/lib/elf:/usr/X11R6/lib:g; s:/usr/i486-linuxelf/bin/:/usr/bin/:g; s:PLATFORM_SUPPORTS_MOTIF  = "TRUE":PLATFORM_SUPPORTS_MOTIF  = "":g;' boot-LINUXELF/m3build/templates/LINUXELF


# http://research.compaq.com/SRC/modula-3/html/patches36.html#gcc-elf says (huh?):
# All of these changes should be made to the template file "boot-LINUXELF/m3build/templates/LINUXELF". You should then copy that file to the file "install-dir/pkg/m3/m3build/templates/LINUXELF" (where "install-dir" is the name of your installation directory, for example, "/usr/local/m3-3.6").

